Counsel:

We write regarding an administrative error that resulted in the inadvertent transmission of privileged attorney work product to your office. The transmittal occurred on [date] when materials were mistakenly attached to an email sent to [REDACTED EMAIL]. The enclosed materials contain attorney mental impressions and work product protected by the attorney-client privilege and the work-product doctrine.

Pursuant to governing law, we request that you promptly take the following steps:
1) Immediately cease review, dissemination, or use of the materials;
2) Locate and delete all electronic copies of the materials and any emails or attachments containing them, and confirm deletion in a return email;
3) Return to us or destroy all physical copies and confirm destruction in writing;
4) Preserve all evidence regarding the receipt, review, storage, or dissemination of the materials pending resolution of this matter;
5) Refrain from using any information contained in the materials in any way in this litigation or for any other purpose.

Please confirm in writing within seven (7) days that the requested steps have been taken. If you contend that any privilege has been waived or if you believe you are required by law or court order to retain or produce any of the materials, please notify us immediately and identify the basis for such contention so we may address the matter with the court if necessary.

We appreciate your cooperation in promptly resolving this matter.

Sincerely,

[REDACTED NAME]
Smith & Associates
